asked about paddy drum seeder
KccAns:
Details of the direct-seeding technology (on per-acre basis):1. Seed rate required - 15 kg
2. Weedicide use is a must, and if needed (in fields where weed problem is high), a
second application at 30 days after sowing is also done in addition to the first
application made within 2 days after sowing.
3. Sprouted paddy seeds are filled to 3/4 level in each of 4 drums, and once the seedr is pulled, seeds fall in 8 rows @ 20 cm width between the rows.
